<td tEditID="c1r1" style=" background-color:#FFFFFF; color:#000000; bEditID:r3st1; bLabel:main; font-size:12pt; font-family:arial;" aEditID="c1r1" locked="0" >
<![CDATA[<div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: right;"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; "><font class="Apple-style-span" color="#000066" size="6">{!Contact.SchoolText__c}</font></span></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: right;"><font class="Apple-style-span" face="'Times New Roman', Times, serif" color="#ff6600" size="4"><i>Chartered By The British Schools Foundation</i></font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: right;"><font class="Apple-style-span" face="Arial, sans-serif" color="#c0c0c0" size="6"><b><i><br></i></b></font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: right;"><font style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);" face="Arial, sans-serif"><br></font></div><div style="text-align: left;"><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;"><font class="Apple-style-span" face="Arial, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="border-spacing: 5px;">Dear&nbsp;{!Contact.Salutation} {!Contact.LastName},</span></font></div><span lang="en-GB"><div style="margin: 0px;"><font face="Arial,Sans-Serif" color="#000000" size="3"><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; margin: 0px;"><br></div><div style="margin: 0px;"><div style="margin: 0px;"><div style="margin: 0px;">As I watch many of you help decorate the school for Christmas the realisation that we are already at the end of the first term of the academic year 2015-2016 has dawned on me. This has given me cause to stop and reflect on the many improvements and achievements that have already taken place this term. The results of our annual parent survey have informed and helped shape this.</div><div style="margin: 0px;"><br></div><div style="margin: 0px;">At the beginning of this term I announced the extraordinary iGCSE results of our Year 10 students and our outstanding Y6 SATs results. School reports are due next week, but I am pleased to say that based on this term’s assessments, all year groups have achieved and progressed far above expected levels.</div><div style="margin: 0px;"><br></div><div style="margin: 0px;"><b>Communication</b></div><div style="margin: 0px;"><b><br></b></div><div style="margin: 0px;">As a school we always need to evaluate our home-school communication and the below improvements have been put in place:</div><div style="margin: 0px;"><ul><li>Introduction of calendar personal to your child’s dates and events has enabled parents to see at a glance what is relevant for their child.</li><li>Increased length of Primary Parent Consultations for Term 2 and student led consultations for Term 3.</li><li>Next academic year will start with a 1-on-1 parent teacher meetings to ensure parents get to know their child’s teacher better early on.</li><li>Focused Class Rep meetings, Primary and Secondary Heads’ forums and annual parent survey enable all to be better informed</li></ul></div><div style="margin: 0px;">&nbsp;&nbsp;</div><div style="margin: 0px;"><b>Enrichment</b></div><div style="margin: 0px;"><ul><li>There are now increased options for sport after school with all students interested in a sport invited to attend team practices</li><li>All school ensembles are expanding with large numbers of students participating on a weekly basis.</li><li>The extended lunch break in Secondary has given students access to a wider range of enrichment activities (31 activities including debating, further maths, graphic design, cricket and fitness).</li><li>For Term 2 we have used feedback from our student councils on popular enrichment activities and we are continually looking to improve choice and quality.&nbsp;</li><li>We have used feedback from our student councils to develop a broader range of quality enrichment activities for Term 2.</li></ul></div><div style="margin: 0px;">&nbsp;</div><div style="margin: 0px;"><b>Environment and Facilities</b></div><div style="margin: 0px;"><b><br></b></div><div style="margin: 0px;">We continuously look to improve our facilities and the environment for students. Some of the changes we hope you have noticed are:</div><div style="margin: 0px;"><ul><li>New classrooms in Secondary that have enabled us to offer smaller tutor groups.</li><li>Major improvements in the shared indoor and outdoor Early Years areas.</li><li>Complete refurbishment of the Primary library.</li><li>Large multi-purpose room in Primary for teaching and group meetings for parents.</li><li>Comprehensive programme to combat mosquitos in collaboration with Rentokil.</li><li>New lightning warning system to keep our students safe.</li><li>IQAir air purifiers in every classroom that remove airborne pollutants, allergens and viruses.</li><li>The number of security guards present in school have increased and we facilitate ongoing training for them. A risk control company has been engaged to advise us on appropriate critical incident procedures.&nbsp;</li><li>Additional CCTV cameras in key areas for improved safety.</li></ul></div><div style="margin: 0px;">&nbsp;</div><div style="margin: 0px;"><b>School Services</b></div><div style="margin: 0px;"><b><br></b></div><div style="margin: 0px;">We have expanded the administration team and work hard to offer excellent service. Some of the areas we have been working on are:</div><div style="margin: 0px;"><ul><li>Primary and Secondary canteen caterers have set up regular parent and student feedback and tasting sessions. We have had favourable feedback from the student council.</li><li>Following parent feedback, the quality of some items of the school uniform has been addressed: The new batch of school bags and Primary/Secondary ties with improved stitching. Early Year ties have an improved elastic band. Two styles of skirts have been introduced for students of different height and preference.&nbsp;</li><li>A new bus service has been introduced for students who are involved in after school Sport, Music or Model United Nations practice.</li></ul></div><div style="margin: 0px;"><br></div><div style="margin: 0px;">I hope to see many of you at our Christmas Concert on Tuesday 8th December at 6pm. For parents who won’t be able to make it I would like to take this opportunity to wish you all an enjoyable holiday. I look forward to welcoming everyone back in the New Year.</div><div style="margin: 0px;"><br></div><div style="margin: 0px;">Warm regards,<br><br></div><div style="margin: 0px;">Janet Brock</div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><b>Headteacher</b></div></div></div><br><br></font></div></span></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: left;"><font class="Apple-style-span" face="Arial, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="border-spacing: 5px;"><div><p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; "><br></p></div></span></font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: left;"><font class="Apple-style-span" face="Arial, sans-serif">{!Contact.SchoolText__c}</font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: left;"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><i><font class="Apple-style-span" color="#ff6600"><b>World Class Education</b></font></i></span></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: left;"><font class="Apple-style-span" face="Arial, sans-serif"><br></font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: left;"><font class="Apple-style-span" face="Arial, sans-serif">__________________________________________________________</font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: center;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="1">{!User.School_List_Email_Footer__c}</font><font class="Apple-style-span" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;" face="Arial, sans-serif" size="1">&nbsp;</font></div>]]></td>
